Description: Vector graphics engine and application framework
 Kotuku is a vector graphics engine and application framework designed for
 creating scalable user interfaces. The framework automatically handles display
 resolution and scaling concerns, allowing developers to focus on application
 logic rather than display technicalities.
 .
 Key features include:
  * Vector graphics rendering with scene graphs
  * SVG support with W3C compliance and SMIL animation
  * Cross-platform display management
  * Lua-based scripting environment (Tiri)
  * Document engine for rich text layout
  * Modular architecture with dynamic loading

